v1.30.6 - SECURITY: LDAP/SCIM provisioning sets roleId (S-6, S-7) + partial S-21

The LDAP path (applyGroupMappings) upserted TeamMembership with only
the legacy ole enum, never oleId. The v1.23 permission resolver
then fell back to the hardcoded DEFAULT_*_PERMISSIONS constants instead
of the team's own (potentially admin-edited) Manager/Member role rows.
SCIM was worse: SCIM-created teams had no system Role rows at all.

Fix:
- Schema: DirectoryGroupMapping.roleId (nullable FK -> Role, SetNull),
  indexed. Migration is additive; no backfill needed because existing
  mappings still carry teamRole.
- New lib/teamRoles.ts: ensureSystemRoles(teamId) is idempotent and
  upserts mgr_/mem_ system roles (matching v1.23 backfill convention);
  systemRoleIdFor(teamId, teamRole) resolves to the right id.
- authService.applyGroupMappings was renamed applyDirectoryGroups and
  made public so tests can drive it without a live OpenLDAP container
  (the S-21 problem). The upsert now sets BOTH role (legacy enum, kept
  as the v1.23 fallback mirror) AND roleId = mapping.roleId ?? systemRoleIdFor(teamId, teamRole).
- scimService.createGroup restructured: create team first, then
  ensureSystemRoles, then upsert memberships with roleId = memberId.
  Same in replaceGroup + patchGroup.
- schemas/directories.ts + directoryService.createMapping accept the
  new roleId. Service validates the role belongs to the mapping team.
- Frontend api.ts types the new field on GroupMapping. The mappings
  management UI doesn't exist on the frontend yet; admins create
  mappings via the API today. UI is v1.31 UX work.

Testing strategy: the existing ldap.test.ts sits behind a live-OpenLDAP
gate (S-21). Putting the roleId assertions there would mean they sit
behind a skip. Instead, new directoryGroupMappings.test.ts drives
applyDirectoryGroups directly (pure Prisma; no LDAP server needed).
Five new tests: JIT MEMBER + roleId, JIT MANAGER + roleId, custom
roleId honored AND second sync does NOT downgrade (the actual bug),
strip-stale-memberships still works, syncRolesFromGroups=false still
no-ops. Plus one new assertion in scim.test.ts (POST /Groups -> every
membership has roleId, team has Manager+Member system roles).

Test infra cleanup: auth.test.ts beforeEach now also wipes Directory
and DirectoryGroupMapping so a prior file's leftover rows don't route
an "unknown user" login through a stale JIT bind (which surfaces a 400
"baseDN missing" instead of the expected 401).

Phase boundary: running openldap as part of standard CI remains the
unfinished part of S-21 - the new tests pin S-6/S-7 correctness; the
end-to-end LDAP smoke still requires the operator to opt in.

Verified: tsc clean (backend + frontend). Full suite 295 passed,
5 skipped (LDAP).